<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="deposit-vt">deposit <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /dɪ'pɒzɪt/    美 /dɪ'pɑːzɪt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>放下：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They deposited the captain into a small boat to let him find his own way home.  
他们把船长放在一条小船上，让他自己想办法回家。</p><footer>人教⑨ – 2</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>存放；寄存；储蓄：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Guests may deposit their valuables in the hotel safe.
旅客可将贵重物品寄存在旅馆的保险柜里。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I deposited ten dollars in my savings account. 
我在自己的储蓄账户上存了10美元。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>付 (订金)；付 (押金)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I had to deposit 10% of the price of the house. 
我必须先付房价的10%作订金。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>使淤积；使沉积：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>As the river slows down, it deposits a layer of soil.
河水流速变慢时，一层泥沙便沉积下来。</p></div></div>